result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 15CM128, 16CM51 & 16CM52 Cases called at 11:56 am. Defendant Nathan W. Reynolds in court with attorney Kristina M. Sanders-Brown.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agreement reached and stated on the record. State moves to amend Count 1 of 15CM128 to Disorderly Conduct in violation of 947.01(1). Attorney Sanders-Brown concurs. 16CM51 & 16CM52 Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.    Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:No Contest to Count 1 of 15CM128 & 16CM52.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in 16CM51 & Count 2 of 16CM52.  Sentencing argument by ADA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Sanders-Brown. Statement by the defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 18 months. CONDTIONS: Anger Management and follow through. AODA and follow through. The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No Contact with A. Salaja. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Attorney fees to be included. Terms of agent.  DNA Sample (16CM52) and Surcharge to both cases ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Appeal Rights Given.
